  <!-- ================================================================
       [06] CONTRIBUTION GUIDELINES
       ================================================================ -->
  <section class="content-section" aria-labelledby="guidelines-heading">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-number">05</span>
      <h2 id="guidelines-heading">Contribution Guidelines</h2>
    </div>
    <p class="section-desc">
      Follow these guidelines to keep the codebase clean and pull requests
      easy to review.
    </p>

    <div class="contribute-guidelines__grid">

      <div class="contribute-guideline">
        <h3>Code Style</h3>
        <ul class="contribute-guideline__list">
          <li>Use <code>'use strict'</code> in all Node.js files</li>
          <li>Use <code>var</code> in route files, consistent with the codebase</li>
          <li>Keep functions small and single-purpose</li>
          <li>No trailing whitespace, 2-space indentation</li>
          <li>Validate all user input at API boundaries</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="contribute-guideline">
        <h3>Commit Messages</h3>
        <ul class="contribute-guideline__list">
          <li>Use conventional commits: <code>feat:</code>, <code>fix:</code>, <code>docs:</code>, <code>refactor:</code></li>
          <li>Keep the subject line under 72 characters</li>
          <li>Reference issues with <code>closes #123</code> in the body</li>
          <li>Write in the imperative mood ("add feature" not "added")</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="contribute-guideline">
        <h3>Pull Requests</h3>
        <ul class="contribute-guideline__list">
          <li>One PR per feature or fix — keep the scope small</li>
          <li>Describe what changed and why in the PR description</li>
          <li>Include screenshots for any visual changes</li>
          <li>Ensure there are no console errors before submitting</li>
          <li>Be responsive to reviewer feedback within a week</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="contribute-guideline">
        <h3>Issues &amp; Discussions</h3>
        <ul class="contribute-guideline__list">
          <li>Search existing issues before opening a new one</li>
          <li>Use the provided issue templates where available</li>
          <li>For bugs, include browser, OS, and reproduction steps</li>
          <li>Feature requests should explain the use case clearly</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ================================================================
       [07] CODE OF CONDUCT
       ================================================================ -->
  <section class="content-section" aria-labelledby="conduct-heading">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-number">06</span>
      <h2 id="conduct-heading">Code of Conduct</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="contribute-conduct__card">
      <h2>Our Community Standards</h2>
      <p>
        We are committed to making participation in the Value.Codes project
        a welcoming and harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless
        of experience level, background, or identity.
      </p>

      <div class="contribute-conduct__principles">
        <div class="contribute-conduct__principle">
          <strong>Be Respectful</strong>
          <p>Treat all community members with respect. Disagreement is
          normal — disrespect is not.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="contribute-conduct__principle">
          <strong>Be Constructive</strong>
          <p>Offer helpful criticism. Focus on the code and ideas, not
          the person who wrote them.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="contribute-conduct__principle">
          <strong>Be Inclusive</strong>
          <p>Welcome contributors of all skill levels. Everyone was a
          beginner once — including the maintainers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="contribute-conduct__principle">
          <strong>Be Patient</strong>
          <p>Maintainers are volunteers. Reviews may take time — follow
          up politely if a week has passed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="contribute-conduct__report">
        Violations of this code of conduct may be reported via
        <a href="/contact">our contact page</a>. All reports are reviewed
        and investigated promptly and in confidence.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>


